      "type": "architecture",
      "title": "Event-driven ingestion pipeline",
      "content": "Telemetry ingestion uses a queue-backed worker pool instead of synchronous HTTP handlers. Bursts of satellite passes were dropping packets under load; the queue decouples receive from process and lets us replay on failure.",
      "confidence": "verified",
      "source": "design review",
      "created_at": "2026-04-02T10:15:00+00:00",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-02T10:15:00+00:00",
      "last_accessed": "2026-05-28T16:40:00+00:00",
      "last_confirmed": "2026-05-20T11:00:00+00:00",
      "access_count": 14,
      "metadata": null,
      "tags": ["pipeline", "queue", "ingestion"]
    },
    {
      "id": "b0000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000002",
      "namespace_id": "a1b2c3d4-0000-4000-8000-000000000001",
      "type": "bug",
      "title": "TLE parser chokes on leading whitespace",
      "content": "Two-line element sets fetched from the mirror include a leading space on line 2 for some satellites. The checksum validator rejected them. FIXED: strip lines before checksum, added regression test with the malformed fixture.",
      "confidence": "verified",
